main event: An unidentified object was reported in Englewood, Ohio on August 3, 1966, observed for 10 minutes.
interesting points: The object was stationary during the observation,The witness noted that the object was absolutely silent,The object was described as a bright light that appeared to be oval-shaped,The object faded out gradually along the eastern horizon,Englewood Police were notified about the sighting on August 8, 1966.
sighted object: a bright oval-shaped light in the sky
witness description: Female, age 52, interested in UFOs but had not reported anything previously
